Secure Sphere Account Deletion Policy
Effective Date: 05/07/2024

1. Introduction

Secure Sphere is committed to protecting your privacy. This Account Deletion Policy explains how we handle account deletions and the associated data from our platform.

2. Requesting Account Deletion

You may request the deletion of your Secure Sphere account by contacting our support team at bcs203165@gmail.com or through the appâ€™s account settings. For security purposes, we may need to verify your identity before processing your request.

3. Deletion Process

Upon receiving a verified account deletion request, Secure Sphere will:

Permanently delete your account and all associated data within 30 days.
Remove your personal information from our active databases and systems.
Ensure any third-party service providers delete your data as per our agreements.
4. Data Retention

Some data may be retained for legal reasons, such as resolving disputes, enforcing our terms, or complying with legal obligations. This data will be securely stored and protected during retention periods.

5. Consequences of Deletion

Once your account is deleted:

You will lose access to all services and data associated with your account.
This action cannot be undone. Deleted accounts cannot be restored.
If you wish to use Secure Sphere services again, you must create a new account.
6. Contact Us

If you have questions about this Account Deletion Policy or the deletion process, please reach out to us at bcs203165@gmail.com.

